                                        <div class="collapse" id="FAQcollapse631" data-parent="#faqListAccordion">Tetenter is not a bank, thus we do not fall under the scope of banking laws and regulations. Like with most forms of investing, peer-to-peer lending carries a degree of risk. We reduce this risk to our investors by conducting thorough due diligence and by taking asset security on every loan, in case the borrower is unable to repay their loan. Tetenter does not guarantee your loans.</div>
