                                        <div class="collapse" id="FAQcollapse632" data-parent="#faqListAccordion">After the credit crunch and the resultant recession, the risk appetite of banks was reduced significantly, which means that banks have tightened their lending criteria. Banks have strict criteria, which is not borrower friendly and thus many loan applications are rejected by banks. 

