                                        <div class="collapse" id="FAQcollapse633" data-parent="#faqListAccordion">An unsecured loan is a loan which does not have any collateral in place, such as land or apartment, and is solely based on a borrower’s credit history and potential ability to repay. Secured loans have assets as collateral so that if a borrower cannot repay the loan, Tetenter's security agent represented by a law firm Triniti will start the asset sales process. Hereby, the risk of losing the money is minimized..</div>
